item.description:
[migrated from NJKpopper blog]
As one ages, time slows down and speeds up simultaneously. Days, weeks, months, and years pass rapidly, but the deep current that runs underneath moves ever more slowly compared to the rapid laying down of foundations that occurs during youth.
All that is by way of apology for NJKpopper&rsquo;s belated discovery of the connections between this&hellip;
[Nirvana singing Where did you sleep last night?] and this&hellip;

[Harmogu singing Шинэ жилийн хүсэл] The inspiration continues&hellip;
I celebrate today for the 3rd time, &ldquo;Harmogu Day&rdquo;, on the anniversary of my serendipitous discovery of Harmogu on YouTube (February 1, 2016). Readers can find my 1st and 2nd anniversary posts on this blog as well.
I am happy that this year has brought the *reading* of Harmogu, in addition to the always intensely pleasurable *listening* to Harmogu. Her elegant and precise language is bringing Mongolian to life for me.
